│ THOUGHT: The crash occurs because replaceAllUsesWith is called with a null replacement when VMap doesn't contain a mapping for exit value E. This can happen if E is a constant or otherwise not cloned during peeling. We should guard the       │
│ lookup and use E itself when no mapping exists to avoid passing null to replaceAllUsesWith.                                                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ sed -i '1216,1218s/P->replaceAllUsesWith(VMap.lookup(E));/{ Value *R = VMap.count(E) ? VMap.lookup(E) : E; P->replaceAllUsesWith(R); }/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/LoopPeel.cpp && submit-patch                                                   │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               │
